{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to changed lines only, not full modified files.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — unit tests of a formatter can miss real failures in diff parsing + prompt assembly across modules. REAL-INFRA: no external system required. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocking diff objects can hide hunk/line-range mistakes. LLM-DEP: no; this is input construction.","test_description":"Run the real diff-ingestion and review-input builder against a fixture PR patch (or temp git repo with commits) where files contain both changed and unchanged suspicious code. Assert the produced review payload includes only changed hunks/lines and excludes unchanged file content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to correct positions in PR diff view.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — local mocks won’t replicate GitHub diff-position semantics (path/side/line/commit context). REAL-INFRA: yes — requires real PR API behavior. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocked API often accepts invalid anchors that real API rejects or remaps. LLM-DEP: no.","test_description":"Create/use a real test PR on GitHub, run inline-comment posting with real API calls, then fetch posted review comments and verify each comment is anchored to expected file/line/side and visible in the PR 'Files changed' diff context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent finds at least one real defect in a PR with a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: yes — correctness depends on model judgment (detecting defect quality), and outcomes can vary across runs. MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: deterministic stubs can pass without measuring true detection capability. REAL-INFRA: external PR API can be fixture-backed; the key failure boundary is model output quality.","test_description":"Use a fixed diff fixture containing a seeded bug (with expected defect category). Execute one real model review step and assert at least one finding correctly identifies the seeded defect (semantic match rubric). Run multiple trials or allow probabilistic threshold to account for model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every summary finding has a matching posted inline comment (no orphan summary items).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — this is a cross-module consistency invariant between finding store, inline post results, and summary renderer. REAL-INFRA: not strictly required; can be validated with local DB/files + fake transport. MOCK-HIDE: unit-level checks can miss ID mapping/dedup/order bugs across components. LLM-DEP: usually no if summary is derived from posted findings.","test_description":"Run finding aggregation, inline-comment post pipeline (with a local fake transport that returns realistic IDs), and summary generation together. Assert each summary item references an existing successfully posted inline comment ID/location, and no extra summary-only findings appear.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"End-to-end sequence on a real PR (read diff → post inline comments → post summary) completes without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP: yes — requires full agent session sequencing across multiple actions and state transitions. REAL-INFRA: yes — real PR/API interactions. LLM-DEP: yes — review findings depend on model output. Failures can arise from orchestration order/retries/tool-step handoff, not just one call.","test_description":"Execute the full autonomous run against a real sandbox PR and repository: ingest live diff, perform model-based review, post inline comments, then post top-level summary. Assert all steps succeed in order, artifacts are present on PR, and run terminates without human input or manual repair.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
